:"What makes grass-fed tallow so good for skin","a1":"Grass-fed tallow mirrors our skin’s natural oils and is loaded with vitamins A, D, E, and K — helping restore moisture, soothe irritation, and support a healthy skin barrier without clogging pores.","q2":"Does it smell like beef?","a2":"Unscented has a faint, natural scent that fades quickly. Our scented versions use pure essential oils like Lavender, Vanilla, and Lemongrass — never artificial fragrance.","q3":"Is it safe for sensitive skin, babies, or acne-prone skin?","a3":"Yes. It’s made from one clean ingredient — 100% grass-fed beef tallow — plus pure essential oil (for scented versions). No seed oils, preservatives, or synthetic fragrance.","q4":"How do I use it?","a4":"Warm a small amount between your fingers and massage into clean, slightly damp skin. A little goes a long way — face, hands, lips, or anywhere that needs nourishment.","q5":"Can it help with eczema, psoriasis, or dryness?","a5":"Many customers use it for exactly that. Tallow’s fatty acids and vitamins can help calm irritation and deeply moisturize, promoting soft, resilient skin.","q6":"My balm softened or melted — is it still okay to use?","a6":"Totally normal. Place the jar at room temp (or 15–20 min in the fridge) to firm back up. Texture may change but performance won’","q7":"How should I store it and how long does it last?","a7":"Keep it in a cool, dry place and out of direct sunlight. If it softens in warm temps, just let it re-firm at room temperature. Best within 12–18 months.","q8":"","a8":"","cta_label":"Questions? Contact Us","cta_link":"https:\/\/hidetallow.com\/pages\/contact","cta_align":"center","cta_bg":"#0e3a27","cta_text":"#ffffff","cta_border":"#0e3a27","cta_radius":15}}},"block_order":["rating_BrHDHK","title","ht_product_description_dminjx","variant_picker","ht_desc_ingredients_eHmyLn","quantity_selector_ct3J3E","price_fHrC4g","subscriptions_app_block_mA96qx","buy_box","custom_liquid_WyWiUr","ht_faq_jAVre9"],"settings":{"